  "bookId": 74,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A lesser demon serving as a city guard. Hardworking and dedicated, yet cheerfully airheaded. An avid admirer of Demon Lord Camilla.",
  "personality": "Always putting on airs of demonic arrogance, but surprisingly diligent at work. A classic case of sharp tongue, soft heart.",
  "like": "Praise, tomato omelet rice, fine desserts",
  "familiarData": "Wukoba is a lesser demon with low magical power who cannot fly, working as a city guard in the boar-folk city. Because Demon Lord Camilla favors the demon race, Wukoba was granted knighthood and quasi-noble privileges despite being only a lesser demon.\nWukoba deeply admires the Demon Lord, training hard in hopes of becoming a greater demon and serving at the Demon Lord's side.\nDiligent and hardworking, Wukoba always arrives quickly whenever a certain troublemaking slave owner causes a commotion. However, being rather gullible, Wukoba is easily fooled with a few words, inadvertently providing cover for that slave owner's secret activities.\nWhile trying to capture a certain illegal merchant, Wukoba has clashed with them several times. Wukoba is the stronger fighter, but the merchant always manages to escape. Wukoba frequently visits the merchant's restaurant for tomato omelet rice without ever recognizing them.\n\nIn short, Wukoba is really easy to handle.",
